    <!-- QUICK ANSWER -->
    <div class="quick-answer">
      <h3>Quick Answer</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Yes — GLP-1 drugs like Ozempic and Wegovy cause significant muscle loss, not just fat loss.</li>
        <li>Studies show 25–40% of weight lost on these drugs can be lean mass.</li>
        <li>Men over 40 are especially vulnerable due to anabolic resistance and existing sarcopenia risk.</li>
        <li>High protein intake (1.2–1.6g per kg of bodyweight daily) is the primary defense.</li>
        <li>Appetite suppression from GLP-1s makes it easy to eat too little protein without knowing it — that's where tracking matters most.</li>
