      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">How much protein should I eat on Ozempic?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Most experts now recommend 1.2–1.6g of protein per kilogram of bodyweight daily (roughly 0.55–0.7g per pound) to help preserve muscle mass while on GLP-1 medications. For a 180-pound man, that's approximately 98–131g of protein per day. The higher end of that range is appropriate if you're also doing resistance training.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Why is muscle loss on Ozempic worse for men over 40?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Men over 40 already experience anabolic resistance — their muscles respond less efficiently to protein signals and require higher per-meal doses of leucine to trigger muscle protein synthesis. GLP-1-driven calorie restriction compounds this, making muscle preservation significantly harder without intentional high protein intake. They're also starting from a position of existing age-related muscle decline.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
